http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Coimbatore/Man-trampled-to-death-by-elephant/article14001330.ece

Anish Abraham (28), an electrician who was riding a two-wheeler near Mango Range, was trampled to death by an elephant near TANTEA Estate in Cherangodu area in The Nilgiris on Thursday.The elephant damaged the two-wheeler and attacked Anish killing him on the spot.Hearing about the death of Anish, residents of the area, who were already agitated over the increase in number of man-animal conflicts, gathered in large numbers and blocked the Cherangodu – Kerala National Highway. The legislator representing the Gudalur constituency, Dravida Mani, also joined the protest.The agitated protesters refused to allow the officials remove the victims’ body. Efforts by the Additional Superintendents to pacify the crowd went in vain. This affected traffic for nearly two hours.As the protest continued and the crowd swelled, police resorted to the use of force to disperse them leading to mild tension.Later, the police sent the body of Anish to Gudalur Government Hospital for post-mortem.The protesters urged the officials to bring in a permanent solution to the issue and not ad-hoc interim solutions. The escalating number of man-animal conflicts had already claimed 15 lives during 2015. The death of Anish was the first in 2016.Police resortedto the use offorce to disperse them leading to mild tension